{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"006cf599-c578-402d-b68e-5f5c38b9dd28","content":"No repo context here, so this is a standalone diagnostic plan. Here's your step-by-step approach:\n\n---\n\n### Phase 1 — Diagnose\n\n```powershell\n# 1. Confirm which SDK(s) are installed\ndotnet --list-sdks\n\n# 2. See what workloads are currently installed (and whether they're in \"manifest-update-needed\" state)\ndotnet workload list\n\n# 3. Check for workload version mismatches\ndotnet workload search maui\n```\n\nLook for: the **maui**, **android**, **ios**, **maccatalyst** workloads. If any are missing or show a version older than the SDK, that's your problem.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2 — Update workloads safely\n\n`dotnet workload update` **is safe** — it updates manifests and packs to match your current SDK band. It does not change the SDK itself.\n\n```powershell\n# 4. Update all workload manifests + installed workloads\ndotnet workload update\n\n# 5. If maui isn't installed at all, install it (pulls android etc. transitively)\ndotnet workload install maui\n```\n\n> **Tip:** Run your terminal as **Administrator** — workload commands write to the SDK install directory.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3 — Fix Android SDK\n\nWorkload update installs the Android build tools, but you still need a valid `ANDROID_HOME`:\n\n```powershell\n# 6. Verify ANDROID_HOME is set and points to a real directory\necho $env:ANDROID_HOME          # or  echo %ANDROID_HOME%  in cmd\n\n# 7. Accept Android SDK licenses (common missing step)\n& \"$env:ANDROID_HOME\\cmdline-tools\\latest\\bin\\sdkmanager.bat\" --licenses\n\n# 8. Install / update required Android SDK components\n& \"$env:ANDROID_HOME\\cmdline-tools\\latest\\bin\\sdkmanager.bat\" `\n    \"platforms;android-34\" \"build-tools;34.0.0\" \"platform-tools\"\n```\n\nIf `ANDROID_HOME` is not set, the .NET Android workload puts its own SDK under:\n```\nC:\\Program Files\\dotnet\\packs\\Microsoft.Android.Sdk.*\\\n```\nCheck your `.csproj` `<TargetFramework>` (e.g., `net8.0-android`) and make sure the corresponding platform is installed.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4 — Verify the fix\n\n```powershell\n# 9. Clean and rebuild\ndotnet clean\ndotnet build -v:normal\n\n# 10. If build succeeds, run on emulator/device to confirm\ndotnet build -t:Run -f net8.0-android\n```\n\n---\n\n### Quick-reference checklist\n\n| Step | Command | What it proves |\n|------|---------|---------------|\n| SDK version | `dotnet --list-sdks` | Correct SDK is active |\n| Workloads | `dotnet workload list` | maui + android installed |\n| Android licenses | `sdkmanager --licenses` | No license errors at build |\n| Clean build | `dotnet build` | Everything resolves |\n\nWork through Phase 1 first and share the output if you hit anything unexpected—it'll tell us exactly which piece is out of sync.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"06cc1ece-9a3a-43c0-a586-d674f9a5c29b","outputTokens":785,"requestId":"1105:2D596F:C67E85:E7F9A3:69FE879E"},"id":"9c72e267-2aeb-4044-982d-69c90f5ff89c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:02:43.660Z","parentId":"e4474364-fbef-4543-bd26-f07725fcee4d"}
